text:
Petar Planić (; born 16 March 1989) is a &lt;a href="Serbs"&gt;Serbian&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="Association%20football"&gt;football&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="Defender%20%28association%20football%29"&gt;defender&lt;/a&gt; who plays for &lt;a href="%C3%9E%C3%B3r%20Akureyri"&gt;Þór Akureyri&lt;/a&gt; in Iceland.
Career.
He started in local club &lt;a href="FK%20Metalac%20Kraljevo"&gt;Metalac Trgovački&lt;/a&gt;. In 2009, he arrived in &lt;a href="OFK%20Beograd"&gt;OFK Beograd&lt;/a&gt;, where he stayed for three seasons, usually playing as a &lt;a href="Defender%20%28association%20football%29%23Full-back"&gt;right-back&lt;/a&gt;. Then he moved to &lt;a href="FK%20BSK%20Bor%C4%8Da"&gt;BSK Borča&lt;/a&gt; and played as a &lt;a href="Defender%20%28association%20football%29%23Full-back"&gt;right-back&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href="Defender%20%28association%20football%29%23Centre-back"&gt;centre-back&lt;/a&gt; too. After &lt;a href="Promotion%20and%20relegation"&gt;relegation&lt;/a&gt; of the club from &lt;a href="Serbian%20SuperLiga"&gt;Serbian SuperLiga&lt;/a&gt;, he left the club, and joined &lt;a href="FK%20Sloga%20Petrovac%20na%20Mlavi"&gt;Sloga Petrovac na Mlavi&lt;/a&gt;. He then joined &lt;a href="Lebanese%20Premier%20League"&gt;Lebanese Premier League&lt;/a&gt; club &lt;a href="Nejmeh%20SC"&gt;Nejmeh SC&lt;/a&gt;
In 2018, he joined &lt;a href="Liga%201%20%28Indonesia%29"&gt;Liga 1 Indonesia&lt;/a&gt; club &lt;a href="PSIS%20Semarang"&gt;PSIS Semarang&lt;/a&gt;. After two short spells in 2019 with &lt;a href="OFK%20Sloga%20Gornje%20Crnjelovo"&gt;OFK Sloga&lt;/a&gt; in Bosnia and &lt;a href="Abahani%20Limited%20%28Chittagong%29"&gt;Chattogram Abahani&lt;/a&gt; in Bangladesh, Planić joined &lt;a href="Maziya%20S%26amp%3BRC"&gt;Maziya S&amp;RC&lt;/a&gt; in the Maldives in January 2020.
On the 18th of March 2021 he signed for Icelandic 1st division club &lt;a href="%C3%9E%C3%B3r%20Akureyri"&gt;Þór Akureyri&lt;/a&gt;
